# The following are a list of URLs, hostnames and IP addresses for mallPatrol.sh
#
# Lines starting with 'http(s)' will use curl for the check
#   If a status code other than 200 is expected, add it as the second word on the line
#   Examples:
#     https://host.domain.net
#     https://host.domain.net 202
#   Spaces in URLs must be html encoded
#
# Lines starting with 'cert' will retrieve the certificate expiration date for the given Server
#  A warning will be raise if the age is within 30 days.
#  To change this default warning age, an second argument can be provided
#  Examples:
#    cert host.domain.net
#    cert host.domain.net 90
#
# Lines starting with 'port' will check if the specified port for the given Server is open
#  Examples:
#    port host.domain.net 27017
#
# Lines starting with 'up' will connect to the specified host (via SSH) and determine the uptime.
#  It is recommended that this only be done for machines where authentication can be done via SSH key.
#  Examples
#    up host.domain.net
#
# Lines starting with 'disk' will connect to the specified host (via SSH) and determine the disk usage of mount points.
#  An optional argument may be provided to change the default usage threshold of 80.
#  It is recommended that this only be done for machines where authentication can be done via SSH key.
#  Examples
#    disk host.domain.net
#    disk host.domain.net 75
#
# Lines starting with 'note' will be echo'ed to the output
#  Examples:
#    note My custom message to show in output
#
# All other lines will be simply perform a ping to the given hostname/IP address
#
# Groups/Sections may be created by adding a line with the group name enclosed in square brackets (ie. `[Stage Server]`).
#   To end a group, use an empty line

note Custom Note
localhost
badname
127.0.0.1
255.1.1.1
https://google.com/ 301
cert google.com 60
port google.com 443

[Group Name]
note This note should be indented
localhost
badname
127.0.0.1
255.1.1.1
https://google.com/ 301
cert google.com 60
port google.com 443


# Be sure to end with an empty line
